                    <div id="contentInt">
                        <div id="mainContent">
                            <div id="printArea">
                                <div id="printAreaContent" tabindex="-1">
                                    
    
        <div class="fbg-row lmRow ui-sortable" data-lm-customclass=""><div data-lm-columnwidth="3" class="lmColumn ui-sortable fbg-col-xs-12 fbg-col-sm-12 fbg-col-md-6 fbg-col-lg-3 column" data-lm-customclass=""><div class="ge-content ge-content-type-gridHTML ui-droppable" data-ge-content-type="gridHTML"><div class="fbg-container-fluid ImageboxOneColumn lmLayoutComponent" data-lm-id="lm1656437705042" data-lm-componenttype="ImageboxOneColumn" data-lm-componenttitle=""><div class="iCreateNoneditableToken" data-lm-tokenid="ImageboxOneColumnTK1" data-icrt-tk-cfg="PlainContent" id="ImageboxOneColumnTK1_lm1656437705042"><div class="fbg-row lb-imageBox cm-datacontainer" data-cm-itemdata="{&quot;items&quot;:[{&quot;img&quot;:&quot;/en/council-and-city-administration/resources/Council/Council-Members-and-Wards/Ward-3---Councillor-Rory-Nisan/Ward3-Councillor-Rory-Nisan-WEB_350x438.jpg&quot;,&quot;imgAlt&quot;:&quot;Councillor Rory Nisan&quot;,&quot;boxHeading&quot;:&quot;Councillor Rory Nisan&quot;,&quot;headColor&quot;:&quot;brand-light&quot;,&quot;linkUrl&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;linkTarget&quot;:&quot;target=\&quot;_blank\&quot; rel=\&quot;noopener noreferrer\&quot;&quot;,&quot;boxContent&quot;:&quot;&quot;}]}"><div class="fbg-col-xs-12"><a href="" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Councillor Rory Nisan" aria-label="Councillor Rory Nisan opens in new window"><img loading="lazy" src="/en/council-and-city-administration/resources/Council/Council-Members-and-Wards/Ward-3---Councillor-Rory-Nisan/Ward3-Councillor-Rory-Nisan-WEB_350x438.jpg" alt="Councillor Rory Nisan"><div class="lb-imageBox_header brand-light">Councillor Rory Nisan</div></a><div class="lb-imageBox_content"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-lm-columnwidth="9" class="lmColumn ui-sortable fbg-col-xs-12 fbg-col-sm-9 column" data-lm-customclass=""><div class="ge-content ge-content-type-gridHTML ui-droppable" data-ge-content-type="gridHTML"><div class="fbg-container-fluid lmLayoutComponent" data-lm-id="lm1656436919680" data-lm-componenttype="StandardOneColumn" data-lm-componenttitle=""><div class="fbg-row"><div class="fbg-col-xs-12"><div class="iCreateDynaToken" data-lm-tokenid="StandardOneColumnTK1" data-icrt-tk-cfg="StandardColumnContent" id="StandardOneColumnTK1_lm1656436919680"><h2 id="toc1">Ward 3 Councillor's Office</h2>
<p>If you have a question or issue with a City service, please contact Service Burlington at <a title="Open new window to email city@burlington.ca" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="mailto:city@burlington.ca" target="_blank" aria-label="city@burlington.ca opens in new window">city@burlington.ca</a> or 905-335-7777 for assistance.</p>
<p>If you have feedback to share directly with Councillor Nisan, please see their contact information below.</p>
<table class="icrtAccordion">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td data-name="accParent">Ward 3 Councillor's Office&nbsp;- Contact Information</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-name="accChild">
<div class="lb-imageBox_content">
<p><strong>Hours of operation:</strong> Monday to Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.</p>
<hr>
<p><strong>Councillor Rory Nisan<br></strong>Tel: 905-335-7777, ext. 7459<br><a title="Open new window to email Ward 3 Councillor Rory Nisan" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="mailto:rory.nisan@burlington.ca" target="_blank" aria-label="rory.nisan@burlington.ca opens in new window">rory.nisan@burlington.ca</a></p>
<strong></strong><hr>
<p><strong>Councillor's Assistant<br></strong>Tel: 905-335-7777, ext. 7565<br><a title="Email the Ward 3 Councillor's Office" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="mailto:ward3@burlington.ca" target="_blank" aria-label="ward3@burlington.ca opens in new window">ward3@burlington.ca</a></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-name="accParent">
<div class="lb-imageBox_content">Deputy Mayor for the Environment</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-name="accChild">
<div class="lb-imageBox_content">
<p>This assignment builds on Councillor Nisan’s experience bringing the Climate Change Emergency Declaration last term of council, and his advocacy on transit.</p>
<p><strong>The portfolio will include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Implementation of our Climate Action Plans</li>
<li>Implementation of our Integrated Mobility Plans, including transit, cycling and walking</li>
<li>Restarting discussions with the school boards on free transit for students, which was put on hold during COVID.</li>
<li>Participating in intergovernmental advocacy on transit and quarries.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-name="accParent">About Councillor Rory Nisan</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-name="accChild">
<p>Rory Nisan was first elected 2018 and in this role he has chaired two budget committees, as well as the Corporate Service, Strategy, Risk and Accountability Committee. He joined the board of directors of the Federation of Canadian Municipalities and the Conservation Halton Board of Directors in 2019 and was appointed Deputy Mayor (Environment) in 2022.</p>
<p>Councillor Nisan’s passions for the city include transportation issues, the environment, ensuring smart growth in the right places, and future-proofing the city to ensure it continues to be the best place to live in Canada.</p>
<p>Prior to joining city council, Councillor Nisan was a career foreign service officer, serving Canada. Among several other roles, he negotiated human rights resolutions at the United Nations, and was responsible for strategic communications at Canada’s delegation to NATO.</p>
<p>Councillor Nisan enjoys taking advantage of all that Burlington has to offer, like BBQing at Lowville Park, taking his kid to the Brant Hills Splash Pad or eating his way through Ward 3’s many fine establishments.</p>
<p>Rory grew up in Brant Hills and attended Lester B. Pearson High School. He holds an honours bachelour degree in political science from Wilfrid Laurier University and a Master’s degree in international affairs.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
